title: TV highlights: The new reality series “Hollywood Cycle” follows fitness instructors at a Los Angeles gym
text:
"Hollywood Cycle" cast member Nichelle Hines at the Cycle House in West Hollywood. (Mike Windle/E! Entertainment) By — Lauren McEwen July 6 at 6:39 PM (All times Eastern)
Judges select their final picks in the last round of “America’s Got Talent” (NBC at 8 p.m.) auditions.
“Return of the Great White Serial Killer: Sharkopedia Edition” (Discovery at 8) investigates a string of shark attacks that took place off the coast of California.
Host Anthony Bourdain focuses on transportation on the next “No Reservations,” (Travel at 8) taking a ride through Malaysia in an elaborately decorated carriage.
In an effort to improve their relationships, four unhappy couples seek perspective by swapping partners for two weeks in “Seven Year Switch” (FYI at 9).
On the next “Zoo," (CBS at 9) Jackson saves a friend from a lion attack in Botswana, an incident that leads experts to believe that large cats may be killing for sport and no longer fear humans.
Kirsten investigates a brain researcher’s strange death and seeks Linus’s help to make sense of a clue left by Ed Clark on the next “Stitchers” (ABC Family at 9).
Brianna has a meeting with casting director, a visit from Siya’s mother brings up some old issues and a new cast member named Chloe joins the “Sisterhood of Hip Hop” (Oxygen at 9).
RETURNING SHOW: On the season four premiere of “Total Divas” (E! at 9), the Bellas deal with the aftermath of quitting the WWE and Eva’s new position in the Divas division causes some issues.
RETURNING SHOW: Celebrities Chrissy Teigen, John Legend, Giada De Laurentiis, Jesse Tyler Ferguson, Jane Krakowski and Zachary Quinto compete in the season three premiere of “Hollywood Game Night” (NBC at 10).
SERIES PREMIERE: “Hollywood Cycle” (E! at 10) is a new reality series about a group of cycling instructors working at a chic Los Angeles studio.
Newly retired and hoping to live off the grid on the Big Island of Hawaii, a woman searches for a $60,000 home-on-wheels on “Tiny House Hunters” (HGTV at 10).
Another teen victim is killed on the next “Scream: The TV Series” (MTV at 10), causing questions about the deaths and creating problems between Audrey and Emma.
“Men in Blazers” comedians Michael Davies and Roger Bennett host “Running of the Bulls Festival and Highlights” (Esquire at 11), featuring live coverage of the annual event in Pamplona, Spain.
— Lauren McEwen
